HEADWORD: Tarpeian
<hw>Tar*pe"ian</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>Tarpeius</ets>, prop., pertaining to <etsep>Tarpeia</etsep>.]</ety>
<def>Pertaining to or designating a rock or peak of the Capitoline hill,
Rome, from which condemned criminals were hurled.</def>⟦br⟧
